==English==

===Etymology===
Latin [[amnestia]], Gr. ?, a forgetting, from ? forgotten, forgetful; 'a priv. + ? to remember: compare with French [[amnistie]], earlier amnestie.  See [[Mean]], v.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]:
** [[WEAE]]: /am.ne.sti/

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''amnesty'''
# Forgetfulness; cessation of remembrance of wrong; oblivion.
<!-- material copied from Webster's Revised Unabridged Dictionary (1913) -->
# An act of the sovereign power granting oblivion, or a general pardon, for a past offense, as to subjects concerned in an insurrection.
<!-- material coppied from dictionary.com -->

===Verb===
